content: Hey there, if I have a caller who says they are a republican, should I engage or mark them as "Strong Trump" and move on?
Did they say Trump specificaly or refuse to say how they are voting?
Did not say how they were voting, just that they were voting Republican and didn't have time to chat when I asked if they wanted to talk more in depth
ok you can just mark that refused.  They won't get a call back but it won't record as a strong Trump.
but would we engage with them? I was marking "strong trump" with a few but was curious what was expected.
if they are just Republicans and are open to engagement/persuasion you can absolutely go down that road.  Its up to you to test if the conversation can be helpful but you can certainly try!
Tell them Liz Chaney is a republican.
